    <title>Java update strategy</title><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
    <!--add author's email address-->
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>
       On &suselinux; 16, Java is delivered and supported in the following versions:
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis>Java 17 </emphasis> &ndash; supported until December 2027
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis>Java 21</emphasis> &ndash; supported until October 2031
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        <emphasis>Java 25</emphasis> &ndash; support date to be confirmed after this version is
        released, expected support date is October 2033.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>
For the available version, the following criteria apply:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Concurrent installation of different versions is supported
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        The Java versions are maintained independently on the &suselinux; minor version release cycle
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Each version is supported across the general support and LTS phase
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Java packages can be updated agile.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
</topic>
